    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for a Medium model risk, Medium model influence, Medium decision consequence context of use. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted because ASTM F1717 defines the single applicable regulatory test condition for this device class, and the tested condition represents the most clinically relevant loading scenario. All three QoIs satisfy both quantitative acceptance criteria (percent difference <10% and E/uval <1.96). The FEA modeling framework is assessed as sufficiently credible to support the regulatory submission decision.",
